In March, China, Cuba and Russia sent medical supplies and experts to help Italy cope with its coronavirus outbreak.
Businessman Jack Ma sent 1.1 million test kits, 6 million masks and 60,000 protective suits to Adís Ababa, Ethiopia, to be distributed by the African Union.
