The Daily Beast obtained a telegram from the U.S. Government describing a stratagem of communications with apparent origin in the National Security Council, and cited the strategy as "All about China".
We have been told that we are trying to convey this message in any way possible, including press conferences and television shows. "Media such as Politics, Foreign Policy and Bloomberg have stated that China's efforts to send aid to the countries affected by the virus are part of a propaganda to gain global influence.
